724728f-a.text:
West Street, center and East Side, ?Forth from Charles Lane,(South of Perry Street and Pier d7,North River).
This view was taken three years before the building of the Canal and 23rd Street section of the West Side Elevated Highway. The date is in the latter part of the Coolidge era and about a week before Charles
A.Lindbergh,Jr's non-atop flight to Paris.
Enoch Morgan's Son's Sapolto Factory may be seen at 7d33-gM4I West Street,adjoining and at tho South corner of Bank Street. The tall white building beyond it is the Bell Telephone Laboratories situated
at the South corner of Bethune Street.

724734f-a.text:
(1)
West Street, east side, from Perry Street, opposite Pier 47, North River, to West 11th (formerly Hammmond) Street, opposite Pier 48. No 425 West Street, at the south corner of West 11th,
is a frame building faced with brick.
March 8, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, two years later, and almost half a year after the opening of the Canal-23rd Street section of the West Side Elevated Highway, underneath which the photographer is standing. Nos. 424 and 425, at and adjoining the south corner of West 11th Street, have been cut down to one-story only. See 11th Street.
April 18, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
